To ensure long-term architectural stability and satisfy the strict validation laws of the **12-Category Complete Mediation Model**, the `@` prefix must be implemented as a **first-class language-level attribute parsed directly into the Abstract Syntax Tree (AST)**.

Treating it as an opaque preprocessor directive that blindly strips blocks before the main parse creates an un-mediated blind spot, violating core principles of your **Syntax**, **AI Authoring**, and **Governance** pillars.

